==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: White mustard
<hw>White mustard</hw>. <def>A kind of mustard (<spn>Sinapis alba</spn>)
with rough-hairy foliage, a long-beaked hispid pod, and pale seeds,
which yield mustard and mustard oil. The plant is also grown for
forage.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

